                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc form="codex">
                            <supportDesc material="perg">
                                <support>Goat parchment (recognisable by the wave like structure of the follicules). Low quality sheets with defective edges (ff. 10-12, 14-15, 18-19, 22-23, 28, 30, 34-35, 39, 42, 47, 50, 55, 59, 61, 65, 67-70, 74-78, 87, 90, 93, 95, 98-101, 103, 106-109, 111, 116-120) and holes: ff. 13 (multiple), 53, 79, 80). The parchment has become semi-transparent in places where the parchment maker scraped the upper layer of the skin on hair side (e.g. f. 30)</support>
                                <extent>
                                    <measure type="leavesCount" quantity="120" unit="folio">120 fols.</measure>
                                    <dimensions type="leaf_current" unit="mm">
                                        <height>180</height>
                                        <width>130</width>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </extent>
                                <foliation>Modern foliation in pencil in the upper right corner of every recto and the lower left corner of every verso.</foliation>
                                <collation>
                                    <formula>I<hi rend="sup">8</hi> (ff. 1-8) + II<hi rend="sup">8</hi> (ff. 9-16, 3 and 6 singletons) + III-VII<hi rend="sup">8</hi> (ff. 17-56) + VIII<hi rend="sup">8</hi> (ff. 57-64, 3 and 6 singletons) + IX<hi rend="sup">8</hi> (ff. 65-72, 2 and 7 singletons) + X</formula>. The first nine quires have quire marks (roman numerals with strokes above and on the left side), written in black ink in the middle of the lower margin on the last quire page (ff. 8, 16, ...).
                                </collation>                                
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
